CVRisk
======
CVRisk is a prototype of a cardiovascular risk calculator. It offers multiple ways of communicating risk. It includes a built in risk model based on Framingham.

LICENCE
=======
See http://github.com/rumi/CVRisk/License.html. 

COPYRIGHT
=========
The copyright holder is the University of Cambridge

AUTHORS
=======
David Spiegelhalter and Mike Pearson

ATTRIBUTION
===========
If you republish or rework this calculator please provide a link back to http://github.com/rumi/CVRisk.

DEPENDENCIES
============
This work builds on the following third party libraries:

AS3-Signals by Robert Penner at http://github.com/robertpenner/as3-signals. 
Robotlegs framework by contributors to http://www.robotlegs.org at http://github.com/robotlegs/robotlegs-framework. 
Signals-extensions-CommandSignal by Joel Hools at http://github.com/joelhooks/signals-extensions-CommandSignal.
SwiftSuspenders by Till Schneidereit http://github.com/tschneidereit/SwiftSuspenders

Compiled '.swc' versions of these libraries are included in this distribution in case future revisions introduce incompatibilities.

LANGUAGE
========
The project is a Flex Builder 4 project. To compile, download the distribution and create a new Flex Web Project 
using the distribution folder as the project folder. The sources may also be compiled using the free Adobe FLEX SDK from
http://www.adobe.com/cfusion/entitlement/index.cfm?e=flex4sdk

